# New demo checklist

When the user says they've copy-pasted this repo (or the current folder) to start a new demo, proactively help rename/update, don't assume it's already done:

- Xcode project/target/scheme name and `PRODUCT_NAME` (currently `NewAppBoilerplateUIKit`)
- `PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER` (currently `com.kamilgomolka.testapp1`) to a demo-specific identifier
- Root folder name and `.xcodeproj` filename to match the new demo
- `MainViewController.title` ("Boilerplate app") to the demo's name
- `TestFeatureViewController` and its "Launch Test Feature" button — this is a placeholder to delete/replace once the real feature exists, not a pattern to preserve
- `LICENSE`/`README` if they mention the boilerplate name specifically

Renaming the Xcode project itself (target, scheme, `.xcodeproj`) isn't a plain text edit — treat it as a project-structure operation and flag if it needs to be done manually in Xcode rather than silently editing `project.pbxproj` by hand.
